# File: specs/bug-fix-write-spec-to-interview-users-when-the-issue-has-open-questions/feature.gherkin
#
# Generated from: specs/bug-fix-write-spec-to-interview-users-when-the-issue-has-open-questions/requirements.md
# Issue: #94
# Type: Defect regression

@regression
Feature: write-spec interviews the user to resolve open questions before drafting

  Before this fix, /write-spec Phase 1 read the GitHub issue and wrote requirements.md
  immediately, with no step to detect unresolved open questions or underspecified
  acceptance criteria. The **Open Questions** field in the Phase 1 review gate was
  display-only. This was fixed by inserting a Gap Detection & Interview step in
  Phase 1 that fires AskUserQuestion per gap in interactive mode, skips cleanly
  when the issue is well-specified, bypasses under unattended mode, and tailors
  its probes to feature vs. defect classification.

  # --- Bug Is Fixed: interactive interview on open questions ---

  @regression
  Scenario: AC1 — interview fires when the issue has unresolved open questions
    Given a GitHub issue #201 whose body contains an "## Open Questions" section with one unresolved item "Should the cache be per-user or global?"
    And the file ".claude/unattended-mode" does not exist
    When I run "/write-spec #201"
    Then before "requirements.md" is written, the skill calls AskUserQuestion once for the unresolved open question
    And my answer "Per-user" is threaded into the drafted requirements
    And the final "## Open Questions" section of "requirements.md" does not list the resolved item

  # --- Bug Is Fixed: interactive interview on malformed ACs ---

  @regression
  Scenario: AC2 — interview fires when acceptance criteria are underspecified
    Given a GitHub issue #202 whose Acceptance Criteria section lists one bullet "The feature should work well" with no Given/When/Then structure
    And the file ".claude/unattended-mode" does not exist
    When I run "/write-spec #202"
    Then before "requirements.md" is written, the skill calls AskUserQuestion with a targeted clarifying question about the missing Given/When/Then structure
    And my answer shapes the AC written into "requirements.md" so it uses Given/When/Then

  # --- Related Behavior Still Works: adaptive skip ---

  @regression
  Scenario: AC3 — well-specified issues skip the interview with no prompt
    Given a GitHub issue #203 whose body has no "## Open Questions" section and whose three acceptance criteria each use Given/When/Then
    And the file ".claude/unattended-mode" does not exist
    When I run "/write-spec #203"
    Then the Gap Detection & Interview step detects zero gaps
    And AskUserQuestion is NOT called by the interview step
    And the skill proceeds directly to drafting "requirements.md"

  # --- Related Behavior Still Works: unattended-mode bypass ---

  @regression
  Scenario: AC4 — unattended mode bypasses the interview even when gaps exist
    Given a GitHub issue #204 whose body has an unresolved open question and one malformed AC
    And the file ".claude/unattended-mode" exists
    When I run "/write-spec #204"
    Then the Gap Detection & Interview step does NOT call AskUserQuestion
    And a one-line divergence note is emitted to stdout stating the interview was bypassed due to unattended mode
    And the skill proceeds directly to drafting "requirements.md" using only the issue body

  # --- Related Behavior Still Works: amendment mode ---

  @regression
  Scenario: AC5 — amendment mode interviews only the new-issue gaps
    Given an existing feature spec "specs/feature-example/" was approved for issue #100 and is now being amended for issue #205
    And issue #205 has one unresolved open question and previously-approved ACs remain valid
    And the file ".claude/unattended-mode" does not exist
    When I run "/write-spec #205"
    Then the Gap Detection & Interview step reads only issue #205's body for gaps, not the existing "requirements.md"
    And AskUserQuestion fires once for the new-issue open question
    And the amendment appends the answer-shaped content to "requirements.md" without rewriting the content approved for #100

  # --- Related Behavior Still Works: defect-tailored interview ---

  @regression
  Scenario: AC6 — bug-labelled issues get defect-specific probes
    Given a GitHub issue #206 labelled "bug" whose body omits the "## Reproduction Steps" section and whose "Expected vs Actual" table is empty
    And the file ".claude/unattended-mode" does not exist
    When I run "/write-spec #206"
    Then the Gap Detection & Interview step classifies the issue as defect
    And AskUserQuestion probes for reproduction steps and expected-vs-actual behavior
    And does NOT ask feature-scope / user-story / success-metric questions
    And the answers populate the Defect Report template sections in "requirements.md"

  # --- Bounded Behavior & Residual Capture ---

  @regression
  Scenario: AC7 — gap detection is bounded and residual items are captured
    Given a GitHub issue #207 with five unresolved open questions
    And the documented per-run interview cap is three questions
    And the file ".claude/unattended-mode" does not exist
    When I run "/write-spec #207"
    Then AskUserQuestion is called at most three times for this run
    And the two unasked questions are recorded verbatim in the "## Open Questions" section of "requirements.md"
    And the cap value and the gap-signal definitions are documented in "skills/write-spec/references/interview.md"
